Nyandarua politicians have been urged to hunt for votes without preaching hatred or propagating malicious lies.Governor Daniel Waithaka and woman representative Wanjiku Muhia on Sunday said residents will choose the leaders they want, not necessarily those who thrive in mudslinging others to gain political mileage.They called for a peaceful election. The two spoke at AC Primary School, Ol kalou, grounds during a prayer meeting convened by the General Conference of Akorino Churches Assembly, Nyandarua chapter, to pray for the nation.&ldquo;The Nyandarua populace is well informed and will separate wheat from chaff during the August election,&rdquo; Waithaka said.